article.description: — Jamir Chaplin and Khalen Robinson scored 13 points apiece to help Little Rock defeat Southeast Missouri State 66-61 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Chaplin, Robinson propel Little Rock over Southeast Missouri State 66-61
article.linkText: Chaplin, Robinson propel Little Rock over Southeast Missouri State 66-61
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- — Jamir Chaplin and Khalen Robinson scored 13 points apiece to help Little Rock defeat Southeast Missouri State 66-61 on Saturday night. Chaplin had seven rebounds for the Trojans (11-10, 5-3 Ohio Valley Conference). Robinson added five assists and four steals. Makhel Mitchell finished 5 of 11 from the floor to finish with 12 points, while adding seven rebounds. The Redhawks (7-14, 2-6) were led by TJ Biel, who recorded 13 points and two steals. Aquan Smart added 11 points and two steals for Southeast Missouri State. Rob Martin also had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
